<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 11:29PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern
Garfield, Daniels, northwestern Roosevelt, central Valley, west
central Sheridan and northwestern McCone Counties through 1230 AM
MDT...
At 1127 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Madoc to near Glasgow. Movement was north
at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of up to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
